                  <msItem>
                     <p>
                        <placeName key="place_111664">Kentford</placeName>.
                        <origDate when="1314">1314</origDate>.
                        Grant from <persName><forename>Thomas</forename> '<surname>Syro</surname>'</persName> and <persName nymRef="Syro"><forename>Jueta</forename> his wife, of <placeName role="person">Nedham</placeName></persName>, to <persName><forename>Walter</forename> <surname>Priour</surname></persName>, <persName nymRef="Priour"><forename>Petronella</forename> his wife</persName>, and <persName nymRef="Priour"><forename>John</forename> their son</persName>, of two acres of arable land in Kenteforde called <placeName type="minor">Schortelond</placeName>, between the land of the <orgName>prioress and convent of Marham</orgName> and that required by the said Walter from the said Thomas and abutting on the meadow of the said Walter called <placeName type="minor">Smalemedwe</placeName>.
                        Dated at <placeName role="date">Nedham</placeName>, on Tuesday [12 Nov] after thefeast of St Martin, 8 Edw. II [1314].
                        Witnesses. <persName><forename>Walter</forename> le <surname>Mercer</surname></persName>, <persName><forename>Gilbert</forename> le <surname>Marseah</surname></persName>, <persName><forename>John</forename> ate <surname>Berwe</surname></persName>, <persName><forename>John</forename> <surname>Howe</surname></persName>, <persName><forename>Ralph</forename> <surname>(Townsend) 'ad capud ville'</surname></persName>, <persName><forename>Thomas</forename> <surname>Beylard</surname></persName>, and others. 
                     The 2 seals are wanting.
                     [Chandler deeds]
                     </p>
